SIMPLE: proclamation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proclamation
<hw>Proc`la*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>proclamation</ets>, L. <ets>proclamatio</ets>. See
<er>Proclaim</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of proclaiming; official or general notice;
publication.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>King Asa made a <qex>proclamation</qex> throughout all Judah; none
was exempted.</q> <rj><qau>1 Kings xv. 22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is proclaimed, publicly announced, or
officially declared; a published ordinance; <as>as, the
<ex>proclamation</ex> of a king; a Thanksgiving
<ex>proclamation</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proclitic</ent>⟦br⟧
